      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p><!-- BIOGHIST REQUIRED -->Director, actor, professor of dramatic art at New York
            University, and organizer and director of the Washington Square Players Repertory
            Company.</p>
         <p/>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>Papers, promptbooks, photographs, lecture notes, correspondence, and theatrical files of
            Somerville. Included are materials from the Washington Square Players and Duke's Oak
            Theatre in Cooperstown, N.Y.</p>
         <p/>
      </scopecontent>
